akes to make artificial intelligence and where it goes wrong. While technical systems present a veneer of objectivity, they are always systems of power. This is an urgent account of what is at stake as technology companies use artificial intelligence to reshape the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aArtificial intelligencexPolitical aspects. 0aArtificial intelligencexSociological aspects. 0aArtificial intelligence. 7aCOMPUTERS / Intelligence (AI) & Semantics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2021 Englishz978311075407008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2021z9783110753837oZDB-23-DEI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073923740uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300252392?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300252392423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300252392/original  a978-3-11-073923-7  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075407-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEIb2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021